                <p n="1">Fortune! Prosperity!</p>
                <p n="1"><supplied reason="subaudible">This is the</supplied> fifth year of Kōrājakesarivarman.</p>
                
                <p n="1-9">
                    For Śrī-Vijaiyamaṅgaladevar of big Śrī-Vāṉavaṉ-mahādevi-caturvedimaṅgalam, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of the northern bank, Ampalavaṉ Paḻuvūr Nakkaṉ alias Rājarāja Pallavaraiyaṉ, having bought in the name of this god <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>itēvar</foreign></supplied> of this Vāṉavaṉ-mahādevi-caturvedimaṅgalam, having bought from <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pakkal</foreign></supplied> the Sabhā of this village for the paddy accrued with the lands of which taxes were remitted <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iṟaiyiḻicciṉa</foreign></supplied>; thus the donation <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nibandham</foreign></supplied> was made for paddy, gold, <foreign>ghee</foreign> and oil, tax on looms <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>taṟippuṭavaikkum</foreign></supplied> and iron <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>irumpukkum</foreign></supplied> that have to be paid to the god <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>itēvaṟkku</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">by</supplied> the northern hamlet <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaṭapiṭākai</foreign></supplied> of Neṭuvāyil whose taxes were remitted and the hamlets <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>piṭākaikaḷum</foreign></supplied> surrounding <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cuṟṟiṉa</foreign></supplied> this Neṭuvāyil.
                </p>
                
                <p n="9-16">
                    As per four <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s for one time <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pōtu</foreign></supplied> of holy food offerings <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruvamutu</foreign></supplied>, as one <foreign>patakku</foreign> of rice <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>arici</foreign></supplied> everyday including the middle of the night <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>atdhayāma</foreign>, that is, <foreign>ardhayāmam</foreign></supplied>, as five <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign>s of paddy daily accrued from the ten kinds <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aint-iraṇṭu vaṇṇattāl</foreign></supplied> of the twice born, as one <foreign>uri</foreign> for one time of <foreign>dhal </foreign>holy food offerings <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paruppamutu</foreign></supplied> and hundred and fifty <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy accrued for one day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāḷḷaikku</foreign>, that is, <foreign>nāḷaikku</foreign></supplied> per year <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>orāṭṭai</foreign></supplied>;
                    
                    for four times including the middle of the night, the paddy for two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of <foreign>dhal</foreign> everyday, as one boiled <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>puḻukku</foreign></supplied> vegetable food offering <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṟiyamutu</foreign></supplied> and one fried vegetable food offering <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>porikkaṟiyamutu</foreign></supplied>, for one <foreign>tūṇi</foreign> and one <foreign>patakku</foreign>, twenty-two <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year.
                </p>
                <p n="16">
                    as one <foreign>patakku</foreign> of paddy for one <foreign>uri</foreign> everyday for four times <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <foreign>ghee</foreign> food offerings for one <foreign>tūṇi</foreign> and one <foreign>patakku</foreign>, twenty-two <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year.
                </p>
                <p n="18">
                    for four times including cumin seeds <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cīrakammum</foreign></supplied>, mustard seeds <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṭukum</foreign></supplied> and pepper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>miḷakum</foreign></supplied> for two vegetable food offerings, as one <foreign>uri</foreign> for one time of curd food offerings <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tayiramutu</foreign></supplied> and sixty <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year;
                    
                    as five <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s everyday for two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s for four times including the middle of the night, as five <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of paddy everyday for one arecanut food offerings <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aṭaikkāyamutukku</foreign></supplied> for four times including the middle of the night everyday, one bundle <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṟṟu</foreign></supplied> of betel leaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>veṟṟilai</foreign></supplied> and twenty arecanuts <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>veṟuṅkāy</foreign></supplied>, five times of arecanut food offerings, two <foreign>tūṇi</foreign>s and one <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign>, eighteen <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year;
                    
                    for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of mixture <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuḻampu</foreign></supplied> of holy sandal paste <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiruccantaṉam</foreign></supplied> everyday and with one <foreign>palam</foreign> and a half everyday of one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of sandal paste for one time for anointment <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tirumeyppūccu</foreign></supplied>, two <foreign>tūṇi</foreign>s and one <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign>, eighteen <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year;
                    
                    as two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s and one <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign> everyday of paddy for three times, with this, camphor <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṟpūramum</foreign></supplied>, juice of storax <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neriyācamum</foreign></supplied>, sandal paste and fragrant woods <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cītāri akilum</foreign>, i.e. red cedar and eagle-wood</supplied>, fourty five <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year;
                    
                    as six <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of paddy everyday for two <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of milk <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>pālu</foreign></supplied> for the holy bath <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭiyaruḷa</foreign></supplied> of him <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āvāṟku</foreign></supplied>, two <foreign>tūṇi</foreign>s and one <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign>, thirty-three <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year;
                    
                    as ten <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one <foreign>kācu</foreign>, as two <foreign>kācu</foreign>s for pairs, a pair for <foreign>dakṣiṇamayanam</foreign> and a pair for <foreign>uttāmayanam</foreign>, of cloths <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paricaṭṭam</foreign></supplied> for him <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āvāṟkku</foreign></supplied>, one <foreign>tūṇi</foreign> and one <foreign>patakku</foreign> and twenty-two <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one day per year;
                    
                    <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> twenty <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for two <foreign>kācu</foreign>s for one day per year;
                    
                    three dresses <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>muṉṟāṭai</foreign></supplied> for one day per year;
                    
                    the sacred bath <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tirunamaṉikai</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy with half <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> for a day per year;
                    
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">for</supplied> the maker of garlands <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tirumālaikaṭṭi</foreign></supplied>, ten <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one <foreign>kācu</foreign> for two as two for one day per year;
                    
                    <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> ten <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy for one <foreign>kācu</foreign>, as one <foreign>kācu</foreign> for two as two for one day per year.
                </p>
                
                <p n="37-39">
                    For the garment for the bath of the idol <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>jala-pavittrattukku</foreign></supplied>,
                    so that there be per year, per day
                    three clothes <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>puṭavai</foreign></supplied>,
                    so that there be for three clothes <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>puṭavai</foreign></supplied> half a <foreign>kācu</foreign>,
                    for half a <foreign>kācu</foreign>
                    five <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy <supplied reason="subaudible">are provisioned</supplied>.
                </p>
                
                <p n="39-41">
                    For five perpetual lamps, 
                    so that there be one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> daily for one lamp,
                    so that there be five <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign>s of paddy <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of <foreign>ghee</foreign> everyday for a lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>viḷakku</foreign></supplied>,
                    per year, 
                    for one day,
                    hundred and fifty <foreign>kalam</foreign>s of paddy <supplied reason="subaudible">are provisioned</supplied>.
                </p>
                
                <p n="42-43">
                    As for twilight lamps,
                    so that there be 
                    eight for early dawn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ciṟukālai</foreign></supplied>,
                    eight for midday <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uccampōtu</foreign></supplied>
                    and fourteen for the night,
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">thus</supplied> for tirthy lamps,
                    daily 
                    one <foreign>nāḻi</foreign> and one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> and of oil <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eṇṇai</foreign></supplied>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"> 
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">are provisioned</supplied>.
                </p>
